x;border-radius:3px;font-size:10px;\">FALLBACK</span></td>\n</tr></table>\n<p style=\"margin:6px 0 0 0;font-size:11px;color:#4b5563;\">Tonight's scan did not surface a 3rd confirmed small-cap (&lt;$2B market cap) catalyst in the 45-day window. Best move: hold cash for VERA outcome. Post-approval rotation target: CAPR near $26 (AdCom July 29). Capital parking fallbacks: ASML or MSFT (Tier A, rotation-playbook.md).</p>\n</td></tr>\n</table>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"height:10px;\"></td></tr>\n\n<!-- CASH DEPLOYMENT -->\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:#161b22;border-radius:8px;padding:18px 20px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 12px 0;font-size:12px;color:#7d9fc1;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;font-weight:bold;\">&#128181; Cash Deployment &#8212; $265.41 Available</p>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background-color:#0d1117;border-radius:6px;padding:14px;\">\n<tr><td>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:11px;color:#e6edf3;\">Deployable: $265.41 &#8722; $6 reserve = <strong>$259.41</strong>. After $3 buy commission: <strong>$256.41 net into position</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:11px;color:#e6edf3;\"><strong>Option A &#8212; Hold for VERA outcome (Recommended):</strong> PDUFA is tomorrow. No new entries today. If approved: partial VERA proceeds &#8594; CAPR entry near $26 (halal + IBKR approval first). This is the right sequence.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:11px;color:#e6edf3;\"><strong>Option B &#8212; Pre-deploy into CAPR (NOT recommended):</strong> 9 shares &times; ~$26 + $3 commission = ~$237. Leaves only ~$28 cash &#8212; below $6 reserve and stacks two binary bets simultaneously. Avoid today.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#f59e0b;font-weight:bold;\">&#8594; Hold cash. Watch VERA tomorrow. Decide Wednesday. Your call.</p>\n</td></tr>\n</table>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"height:10px;\"></td></tr>\n\n<!-- IBKR INTELLIGENCE OFFLINE -->\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:#0a0f1a;border-left:3px solid #3b82f6;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 18px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 4px 0;font-size:11px;color:#3b82f6;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;font-weight:bold;\">&#128202; IBKR Intelligence &#8212; 6 July 2026</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#f59e0b;\">&#9888; All IBKR intelligence unavailable &#8212; connector offline. Account performance (TWR/MWR), sector allocation, and theme data all N/A. Re-run when IBKR is connected.</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"height:10px;\"></td></tr>\n\n<!-- EDUCATION #18 -->\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:#0f172a;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:18px 20px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 4px 0;font-size:11px;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;font-weight:bold;\">&#128218; Concept #18 of 30</p>\n<h3 style=\"margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:14px;color:#e2e8f0;font-weight:bold;\">Short Interest &amp; Squeeze Setups &#8212; why VERA could gap 80% on approval, not just 40%</h3>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:12px;color:#cbd5e1;line-height:1.65;\">Short interest is the percentage of shares sold short &#8212; traders who borrowed stock and sold it, betting the price falls. Above 20% is elevated; above 40% is squeeze territory. Heading into tomorrow's VERA PDUFA, expect meaningful short interest from traders betting against accelerated approval. Here's the mechanic: if the FDA approves, those shorts must buy back to limit losses. Their forced buying hits the ask at any price, pushing the stock higher, triggering more forced covering &#8212; a self-feeding loop. That's why PDUFA approvals sometimes produce +60&#8211;80% opens rather than the +30% the pure fundamental math would suggest: the squeeze amplifies the re-rating. Conversely, on a CRL, longs rush to exit and shorts pile on &#8212; the down move gets steeper too. The number to check in your broker app before the print: <strong>days-to-cover</strong> (short interest &divide; average daily volume). If VERA shows 8&#8211;10 days-to-cover, that's 8&#8211;10 days of normal buying volume compressed into one session &#8212; pure gasoline on the fire if approved.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-size:11px;color:#94a3b8;\"><strong>To use it:</strong> Find VERA short interest % on Fintel or your broker. If above 20% of float, the squeeze premium on approval is real &#8212; your $55 TP1 is conservative and the initial gap could blow through it. Set a limit sell above TP1, not at it, to avoid the gap-and-fade. If short interest is low, the move reflects fundamentals only and price discovery is slower.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;font-style:italic;\">Also today: <strong>Float</strong> &#8212; shares actually available to trade (outstanding minus locked-up insider holdings). Smaller float = fewer shares to cover = amplified squeeze.</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"height:10px;\"></td></tr>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:10px 8px;text-align:center;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 3px 0;font-size:10px;color:#374151;\">&#9888; IBKR connector unavailable &#8212; all price/P&amp;L data is N/A. Cost basis from portfolio.json (updated 2026-07-05T06:00+03:00). Verify all numbers in broker app before acting.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 3px 0;font-size:10px;color:#374151;\">This is research, not financial advice. Halal status re-verified quarterly via Musaffa (AAOIFI standards).</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#1f2937;\">&#169; 2026 Abbas Al Madani &middot; Halal Aggressive Growth &middot; Generated Monday 6 July 2026 &middot; Kuwait (UTC+3)</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n</td></tr>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>"\n}\n